A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 12, 2025, as Afterschool Day at the state capitol; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, afterschool programs provide innovative hands-on opportunities for youth to
4 re-engage in their learning and connect with caring adults and peers in a safe and supportive
5 environment; and
6 WHEREAS, afterschool programs improve academic performance and outcomes by
7 increasing school day attendance, reducing grade retention, and improving classroom
8 behavior; and
9 WHEREAS, afterschool programs improve youth mental health by promoting healthy habits,
10 developing positive decision-making skills, and building resiliency and coping skills; and
11 WHEREAS, afterschool programs support working families and build stronger communities
12 by ensuring children are safe and productive after the regular school day ends and involving
13 parents, community leaders, businessmen, and adult volunteers in the lives of young people;
14 and
